It works okay in FCEUX.....uhhh remember to set the scroll to $00 and $00 for now to keep the name table on #1 if you aren't using them, thats what I see. Do that by at the end of the NMI store $00 to the scroll registers, $2005 IIRC, And you do it twice IIRC. Not 100% sure about that though.<br /><br /><br />It's a good start, I've never went to college and in the middle of high school and would reccomend doing 6809 after 6800, It's a lot more registers and a lot easier to do stuff with. 6809 has X and Y 16 bit pointers, A and B 8-Bit accumulators, 2 stacks and it's got lots of nice instruction <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" /> I like to control HD44780 displays with it, as we have a TON of them for cheap.<br /><br /><br /><br />Well keep trying to add on or even better, tidy up your code for now and try to find new and more efficent ways of doing stuff.<br /><br /><br />EDIT:<br /><br />Haha looks like I just teested the program, the others above me read the program faster then I looked at what it does on the screen.....well thats the last time I be lazy <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4311">3gengames</a> — Sun Jul 25, 2010 12:22 pm</p><hr />
