<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6685&amp;p=64869#p64869"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[I'm starting to get the hang of this]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6685&amp;p=64869#p64869"><![CDATA[
What emulator are you using? It doesn't work in Nintendulator, one of the most accurate emulators around.<br /><br />Looking at the code, I have to say that you were very careless. You forgot to do any initialization whatsoever. You don't disable interrupts, initialize the stack, wait for the PPU to warm up, nothing.<br /><br />Also, you enable PPU rendering right away, and then set up the palette without checking if you are in Vblank.<br /><br />You have to pay attention to details like these, or else your programs won't work well on hardware.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Sun Jul 25, 2010 12:17 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
